### /v1/chat/completions — Tool-Calling Test Cases
### Compatible with VS Code REST Client / IntelliJ HTTP Client
### Base URL: http://localhost:8000
### Endpoint:  POST /v1/chat/completions  (mounted by app.include_router(chat_router, prefix="/v1") in app/main.py)
###
### What this file covers:
### - Section 1: Health & tool registry (sanity check)
### - Section 2: Base LLM (no tools)        — verifies the proxy passes through plain chat
### - Section 3: Each tool exposed alone    — verifies registration + invocation per tool
### - Section 4: All tools exposed together — verifies the LLM picks the right tool
### - Section 5: Parallel + chained tools   — verifies multi-tool / multi-round behavior
### - Section 6: tool_choice variants       — verifies "auto", "none", and forced tool
###
### Notes:
### - Default model is meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct. If a tool doesn't fire, swap to
###   "openai/gpt-4o-mini" or "anthropic/claude-3.5-haiku" — they call tools more reliably.
### - All four tools (get_weather, generate_email, web_search, run_python) are also
###   registered server-side. The proxy executes the call locally and returns the FINAL
###   answer, not the raw tool_calls (unless none of the requested tools are in TOOL_MAP).
### - Authorization header is shown commented out — uncomment if PROXY_API_KEY is set.
### ============================================================


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### SECTION 1: Health & Tool Registry
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


### 1.1 Health check
GET http://localhost:8000/

### 1.2 List available tools
GET http://localhost:8000/tools


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### SECTION 2: Base LLM (no tools)
### Verifies plain chat passthrough — no tool loop, just one round-trip.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


### 2.1 Base LLM — non-streaming
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "What is the capital of France? Answer in one sentence." }
  ]
}

### 2.2 Base LLM — streaming (SSE)
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Count from 1 to 5." }
  ],
  "stream": true
}

### 2.3 Base LLM with system prompt
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "system", "content": "You are a concise assistant. Reply in under 20 words." },
    { "role": "user",   "content": "Explain what a REST API is." }
  ]
}

### 2.4 Base LLM — multi-turn conversation
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "system",    "content": "You are a helpful assistant." },
    { "role": "user",      "content": "My name is Jaydip." },
    { "role": "assistant", "content": "Nice to meet you, Jaydip!" },
    { "role": "user",      "content": "What is my name?" }
  ]
}


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### SECTION 3: Single Tool Tests
### Each request exposes ONE tool. Verifies that tool is invoked
### and the final answer comes back populated by the tool's output.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


### 3.1 get_weather — non-streaming
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "What is the weather in Mumbai right now?" }
  ],
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "city": { "type": "string", "description": "The city name to get weather for" }
          },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 3.2 get_weather — streaming
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "What is the weather in Delhi?" }
  ],
  "stream": true,
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "city": { "type": "string", "description": "The city name to get weather for" }
          },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 3.3 generate_email — non-streaming
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Write a formal email to john@example.com about the project deadline being extended by one week." }
  ],
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "generate_email",
        "description": "Generate a formatted email with the given recipient, subject, and optional tone",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "to":      { "type": "string", "description": "Email recipient address" },
            "subject": { "type": "string", "description": "Email subject line" },
            "tone":    { "type": "string", "description": "Tone of the email (e.g. formal, casual)", "default": "formal" }
          },
          "required": ["to", "subject"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 3.4 generate_email — streaming
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Send a casual email to alice@example.com about lunch plans tomorrow." }
  ],
  "stream": true,
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "generate_email",
        "description": "Generate a formatted email with the given recipient, subject, and optional tone",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "to":      { "type": "string" },
            "subject": { "type": "string" },
            "tone":    { "type": "string", "default": "formal" }
          },
          "required": ["to", "subject"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 3.5 web_search — non-streaming
### Requires duckduckgo-search package; install with `uv add duckduckgo-search` if missing.
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Search the web for the latest news about FastAPI." }
  ],
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "web_search",
        "description": "Search the web for real-time information, facts, news, or anything not in the model's training data",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "query":       { "type": "string", "description": "The search query" },
            "max_results": { "type": "integer", "description": "Maximum number of results to return (default 3)", "default": 3 }
          },
          "required": ["query"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 3.6 web_search — streaming
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Find me 2 recent articles about DSPy framework." }
  ],
  "stream": true,
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "web_search",
        "description": "Search the web for real-time information, facts, news, or anything not in the model's training data",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "query":       { "type": "string" },
            "max_results": { "type": "integer", "default": 3 }
          },
          "required": ["query"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 3.7 run_python — non-streaming
### Verifies the server-side Python sandbox (subprocess + 15s timeout).
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Use Python to compute the sum of squares from 1 to 100. Show the result." }
  ],
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "run_python",
        "description": "Execute a Python code snippet on the server and return its output. Use this for file operations (move, copy, delete, create directories), math calculations, data processing, or any task that Python can handle. Always use print() to output results.",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "code": { "type": "string", "description": "Valid Python source code to execute. Use print() to produce output." }
          },
          "required": ["code"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 3.8 run_python — streaming
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Use Python to print the first 10 Fibonacci numbers." }
  ],
  "stream": true,
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "run_python",
        "description": "Execute a Python code snippet on the server and return its output. Use print() to produce output.",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "code": { "type": "string" }
          },
          "required": ["code"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### SECTION 4: All Tools Exposed — LLM Picks
### All 4 tools registered. Verifies the model selects the right one
### per prompt without being told which to use.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


### 4.1 All-tools — weather prompt → expects get_weather
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "What's the weather in Surat?" }
  ],
  "tools": [
    { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "get_weather",    "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",                                                                "parameters": { "type": "object", "properties": { "city":  { "type": "string" } }, "required": ["city"] } } },
    { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "generate_email", "description": "Generate a formatted email with the given recipient, subject, and optional tone",                                  "parameters": { "type": "object", "properties": { "to":    { "type": "string" }, "subject": { "type": "string" }, "tone": { "type": "string", "default": "formal" } }, "required": ["to", "subject"] } } },
    { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "web_search",     "description": "Search the web for real-time information",                                                                         "parameters": { "type": "object", "properties": { "query": { "type": "string" }, "max_results": { "type": "integer", "default": 3 } }, "required": ["query"] } } },
    { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "run_python",     "description": "Execute a Python code snippet on the server and return its output. Use print() to produce output.",                "parameters": { "type": "object", "properties": { "code":  { "type": "string" } }, "required": ["code"] } } }
  ]
}

