### 4.5 All-tools — no-tool-needed prompt → expects no tool call
### Verifies the model doesn't hallucinate a tool call when not required.
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Who was the first president of the United States?" }
  ],
  "tools": [
    { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "get_weather",    "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",                                                                "parameters": { "type": "object", "properties": { "city":  { "type": "string" } }, "required": ["city"] } } },
    { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "generate_email", "description": "Generate a formatted email with the given recipient, subject, and optional tone",                                  "parameters": { "type": "object", "properties": { "to":    { "type": "string" }, "subject": { "type": "string" }, "tone": { "type": "string", "default": "formal" } }, "required": ["to", "subject"] } } },
    { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "web_search",     "description": "Search the web for real-time information",                                                                         "parameters": { "type": "object", "properties": { "query": { "type": "string" }, "max_results": { "type": "integer", "default": 3 } }, "required": ["query"] } } },
    { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "run_python",     "description": "Execute a Python code snippet on the server and return its output. Use print() to produce output.",                "parameters": { "type": "object", "properties": { "code":  { "type": "string" } }, "required": ["code"] } } }
  ]
}


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### SECTION 5: Parallel + Chained Tools
### Verifies the multi-tool / multi-round behavior in llm_service.py.
### Parallel = multiple tool calls in ONE round (asyncio.gather kicks in).
### Chained  = each round needs the previous round's tool output.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


### 5.1 Parallel — weather in two cities (one round, two get_weather calls)
### Strong models bundle these in one round; Llama-3.1-8B may serialize across two rounds.
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "openai/gpt-4o-mini",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "What is the current weather in both Delhi and Mumbai?" }
  ],
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": { "city": { "type": "string" } },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 5.2 Parallel — weather in three cities
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "openai/gpt-4o-mini",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Give me the weather in Delhi, Mumbai, and Chennai right now." }
  ],
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": { "city": { "type": "string" } },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 5.3 Chained — weather then email summary (multi-round)
### Round 1: get_weather → Round 2: generate_email (using weather result) → Round 3: final text.
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "openai/gpt-4o-mini",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Check the weather in Ahmedabad and then email a one-line summary to team@company.com." }
  ],
  "tools": [
    { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "get_weather",    "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",                                                                "parameters": { "type": "object", "properties": { "city": { "type": "string" } }, "required": ["city"] } } },
    { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "generate_email", "description": "Generate a formatted email with the given recipient, subject, and optional tone",                                  "parameters": { "type": "object", "properties": { "to":   { "type": "string" }, "subject": { "type": "string" }, "tone": { "type": "string", "default": "formal" } }, "required": ["to", "subject"] } } }
  ]
}

### 5.4 Chained — search then summarize via Python
### Round 1: web_search → Round 2: run_python (count/process results) → Round 3: final text.
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "openai/gpt-4o-mini",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Search the web for 'Python 3.13 new features' and use Python to print the number of results returned." }
  ],
  "tools": [
    { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "web_search", "description": "Search the web for real-time information", "parameters": { "type": "object", "properties": { "query": { "type": "string" }, "max_results": { "type": "integer", "default": 3 } }, "required": ["query"] } } },
    { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "run_python", "description": "Execute a Python code snippet on the server and return its output.", "parameters": { "type": "object", "properties": { "code":  { "type": "string" } }, "required": ["code"] } } }
  ]
}

### 5.5 Multi-tool combined — weather + email + python (full pipeline, streaming)
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "openai/gpt-4o-mini",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Get the weather in Jaipur, write a Python one-liner to convert that temperature from Celsius to Fahrenheit, then email the result to traveler@example.com." }
  ],
  "stream": true,
  "tools": [
    { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "get_weather",    "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",                                "parameters": { "type": "object", "properties": { "city":  { "type": "string" } }, "required": ["city"] } } },
    { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "generate_email", "description": "Generate a formatted email with the given recipient, subject, and optional tone",  "parameters": { "type": "object", "properties": { "to":    { "type": "string" }, "subject": { "type": "string" }, "tone": { "type": "string", "default": "formal" } }, "required": ["to", "subject"] } } },
    { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "run_python",     "description": "Execute a Python code snippet on the server and return its output.",              "parameters": { "type": "object", "properties": { "code":  { "type": "string" } }, "required": ["code"] } } }
  ]
}


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### SECTION 6: tool_choice Variants
### Verifies "auto" (default), "none" (forbid tools), and forced specific tool.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


### 6.1 tool_choice: "auto" — explicit default
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "What is the weather in Pune?" }
  ],
  "tool_choice": "auto",
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": { "city": { "type": "string" } },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 6.2 tool_choice: "none" — must NOT call any tool even if relevant
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "What is the weather in London?" }
  ],
  "tool_choice": "none",
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": { "city": { "type": "string" } },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 6.3 tool_choice: forced specific tool — must call get_weather even off-topic
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Tell me about Jaipur." }
  ],
  "tool_choice": { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "get_weather" } },
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": { "city": { "type": "string" } },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### SECTION 7: Edge Cases
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


### 7.1 Unregistered tool — proxy should return raw tool_calls (BFCL pass-through)
### `book_flight` is NOT in TOOL_MAP → llm_service.py:50 short-circuits and forwards
### the model's raw tool_calls without local execution.
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "openai/gpt-4o-mini",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Book a flight from Delhi to London for tomorrow." }
  ],
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "book_flight",
        "description": "Book a flight between two cities on a specific date",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "from": { "type": "string" },
            "to":   { "type": "string" },
            "date": { "type": "string" }
          },
          "required": ["from", "to", "date"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 7.2 Default model — model field omitted, server falls back to DEFAULT_MODEL
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "What is the weather in Bengaluru?" }
  ],
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": { "city": { "type": "string" } },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 7.3 Auth-required server (only meaningful if PROXY_API_KEY is set)
POST http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json
# Authorization: Bearer your-proxy-api-key-here

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Ping." }
  ]
}
